The paper deals with dimension reduction and distance preservation, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of binary strings and Hamming distance suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the experiments on real data sets suggest a possible connection to social and information networks (cs.SI).
